  Title: The Age of Naval Artillery
  Description: The introduction of ship-mounted cannons has begun to change warfare
    at sea. Though boarding actions remain common, Gun Carracks can now engage enemy
    vessels and coastal fortifications with artillery before closing for battle.
    These versatile warships combine ocean-going endurance with the growing power
    of gunpowder.
  GeoLocalizationID: 
  Notes: 
